Merge pull request #775 from e-motiv/patch-1

autoload - Windows & slash forgot?

autoload - Windows & slash forgot?

I added 2 DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR's because:
1. Makes it compatible with windows server
  (I use linux server, but test everything at home with EasyPHPServer on Windows and people might use IIS in general too)
2. I'm not sure if this was a bug or typically windows again, but it seems that __DIR__ doesn't have a trailing directory separator, so we have to add one. If this is not the same on linux, the latter case some more coding needs to be done on the first DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR not to be doubled for linux

Special case handling of Live authentication

Applied a workaround to solve the fact that Windows Live does not allow parameters in redirect URLs,
causing failure in this case:
http://mywebsite.com/path_to_hybridauth/?hauth.done=Live
So if the case is Live authentication, then redirect url should be
http://mywebsite.com/path_to_hybridauth/live.php

Create live.php

Windows Live authentication does not allow redirect URLs to contain any parameters, 
Therefore live.php is an alternative to index.php which initializes $_REQUEST['hauth_done'] = 'Live'; before proceeding with authentication.
As a result The redirect URL to be used in Windows Live authentication settings will become:
http://mywebsite.com/path_to_hybridauth/live.php
instead of:
http://mywebsite.com/path_to_hybridauth/?hauth.done=Live
Fixed issue with empty redirect mode configuration preventing redirection.

Update OAuth2Client.php

Added PATCH wrapper to library which updates event to Google Calendar.

Api Call

$adapter->api()->patch($url,$data);

Parameter:
$url = url from calendar api including eventid
           e.g; $url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/primary/events/'.$id;
$data = Array consisting values to update.

Update OAuth2Client.php

I have created  a Delete Wrapper which will delete the event from calendar api.

User have to use following lines to delete an event.

Api call for delete.

$adapter>api()->delete($urls);
parameter:

$urls: this will be the delete url including the event it. e.g $urls = 'https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/primary/events/'.$id;  

Please let me know if you accept or discard my change.

Thanks,
Hassan Mehmood 
PHP developer
Pakistan

Revert a hack that blocks scope flexibility

Hardcoding the scope disables the settings that are defined in the application itself, and blocks per-implementation scope configuration.
The scope can be defined when creating/updating a LinkedIn app, so it's useless to hack it.
The scope should be hardcoded only if it can be set elsewhere, out of the library, so that implementation can define their own scope directly, so not as a constant.
Application scope setting seems the most flexible solution for the moment.
